<P>Dr. MAYHEW's DISCOURSE ON POPISH IDOLATRY.</P>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="title page">
<PB REF="010068_0002_0F7C7583FB0CE5C8" MS="y">
<P>POPISH IDOLATRY: A DISCOURSE DELIVERED IN THE CHAPEL OF HARVARD-COLLEGE IN CAMBRIDGE, NEW-ENGLAND, MAY 8. 1765. AT THE LECTURE founded by the Honorable PAUL DUDLEY, ESQUIRE. BY JONATHAN MAYHEW, D. D. PASTOR OF THE WEST CHURCH IN BOSTON.</P>
<Q><P>&mdash;If any man that is called a brother be &mdash; an idolater&mdash; with &s;uch an one no not to eat.</P>
<BIBL>Apo&s;tle PAUL.</BIBL></Q>
<Q><P>&mdash;Be not deceived: Neither fornicators, nor idolaters&mdash; &s;hall inherit the kingdom of God.</P>
<BIBL>IDEM.</BIBL></Q>
<Q><P>&mdash;Idolaters&mdash;&s;hall have their part in the lake which burneth with fire and brim&s;tone; which is the &s;econd death.</P>
<BIBL>Apo&s;tle JOHN.</BIBL></Q>
<Q><P>&mdash;Without are dogs&mdash;and idolaters&mdash;</P>
<BIBL>ID.</BIBL></Q>
<P>BOSTON: Printed by R. &amp; S. DRAPER, EDES &amp; GILL, and T. &amp; J. FLEET. MDCCLXV.</P>
